Others moaned and wept and uttered heart-rending cries because of the ulceration of their male organ.

00:20:35.400 --> 00:20:42.600
Gruenpeck's description is historically important: It is the first unchallenged record of syphilis in the world.

00:20:44.190 --> 00:20:49.460
He accurately portrays the distinct stages of the disease as they are still understood today.

00:20:50.660 --> 00:20:57.360
The first stage of the disease really just involves ulceration at the site of infection,

00:20:57.360 --> 00:20:59.620
so things like genital ulcers.

00:20:59.780 --> 00:21:02.880
The swelling of the glans was followed by an abscess,

00:21:02.880 --> 00:21:06.360
from which the putrid smelling pus flowed for a full month.

00:21:06.800 --> 00:21:12.820
The second stage, which occurs about three to six months after infection, you get a generalized rash.

00:21:13.800 --> 00:21:20.380
They experienced intense pains in head and bones, and soon boils appears all over the body.

00:21:21.960 --> 00:21:26.899
It's the third phase where you get considerable ulceration on the skin.

00:21:28.770 --> 00:21:33.109
The person wouldn't be feeling too good, I don't think, and wouldn't look very nice, either.

00:21:35.040 --> 00:21:39.080
You can relate their bone lesions quite nicely to ulcerations of the skin.

00:21:39.780 --> 00:21:46.670
Imagine a boil or an ulcer on the skin, and that's tracking down to these lesions on this on the skull.

00:21:47.310 --> 00:21:49.310
Not very nice.

00:21:57.220 --> 00:22:01.980
And I would thinking you've got an infectious lesion that's active in the mouth,

00:22:01.980 --> 00:22:05.360
you're going to have somebody who's got a pretty awful bad breath.

00:22:06.960 --> 00:22:11.900
If you can imagine this person with these bones inside their body,

00:22:11.920 --> 00:22:19.980
you would expect swelling, quite a lot of pain and heat just as a result of inflammation.

00:22:22.620 --> 00:22:29.480
The other thing that you get in the third phase of syphilis is what they call "general paralysis of the insane."

00:22:43.700 --> 00:22:51.460
This was more than just another plague. It was a disease which brought to the sufferer not only pain, but shame.

00:22:54.780 --> 00:23:00.800
In the fervently religious Christian Europe of the time, this new disease represented the wrath of God,

00:23:01.470 --> 00:23:03.949
punishing wicked people for their immorality.

00:23:08.100 --> 00:23:12.020
As Gruenpeck describes the horror at the end of the 15th century,

00:23:12.300 --> 00:23:15.520
no one seemed to know where syphilis had come from,

00:23:15.520 --> 00:23:19.840
and of course nobody was willing to accept the place of origin for this disease as their own.

00:23:20.530 --> 00:23:27.899
He calls it the French disease; the French called it the Neapolitan disease; the Germans called it the Spanish itch.

